title: For Sale/Trade:  Colt Lightweight Commander Series 70 1911 .45
postcontent: I have a Colt "Lightweight Commander" Series 70 1911 in 45. According to http://www.sightm1911.com/lib/history/Commander_evolution.htm it is a "Light weight Commander" which were produced from 1970-1983. The light weight commanders being the first 1911s that used aluminum frames instead of steel. After doing the serial number look up on Colts website I was able to confirm that the manufacture date was 1973. It shows its age with a few cosmetic flaws but still functions great and feels very solid. It comes with 1 magazine and an aftermarket hard case.
